versions.description: Windows Platform Support, ListView updates, Vector overlays in maps
versions.name: Release 4.1.0

status.description: The issue is considered finished, the resolution is correct. Issues which are closed can be reopened.

fields.description:
The following example crashes when you comment out the {{mapType}} line:

{code:javascript}
var win = Ti.UI.createWindow();
var Map = require('ti.map');
var coords = {latitude: 37.3689, longitude: -122.0353};
var radius = 5000;
 
var map = Map.createView({
//    mapType: Map.NORMAL_TYPE,
    region: {latitude: 37.3689, longitude: -122.0353, latitudeDelta: 1, longitudeDelta: 1 },
});
 
var circle = Map.createCircle({
      center: coords,
      radius: radius
}); 

var polygon = Map.createPolygon({
	points: [{latitude: 36.3689, longitude: -122.0353},{latitude: 35.3689, longitude: -102.0353},{latitude: 37.3639, longitude: -122.0348}],
	strokeColor: "#f00",
	strokeWidth: 4
});

var polyline = Map.createPolyline({
	points: [{latitude: 37.3689, longitude: -122.0353},{latitude: 35.3689, longitude: -102.0353},{latitude: 37.3639, longitude: -122.0348}],
	strokeColor: "#ff0",
	strokeWidth: 4
});
 
win.add(map);
map.addCircle(circle);
map.addPolygon(polygon);
map.addPolyline(polyline);

setTimeout(function() {
	map.removeCircle(circle);
	map.removePolygon(polygon);
	map.removePolyline(polyline);
}, 5000);

win.open();
{code}

fields.summary: iOS: Map Crashes with SIGSEGV if you add a vector to a map with no mapType set

comments.body: Issue resolved, the addCircle proxy method was not performed on the right thread. Same problem with polygones and polylines. PR coming next few days!
[~fokkezb]: PR pending (https://github.com/appcelerator-modules/ti.map/pull/109), updated example to cover all adding and removing tests of possible vectors.

CR and FT passed. PR merged.
Titanium_mobile PR: https://github.com/appcelerator/titanium_mobile/pull/6979

No crash when vector added on a map and no mapType set.

Verified on:
Mac OS 10.10.4
Ti SDK: 4.1.1.v20150802200935 , 4.2.0.v20150803003621
ti.map: 2.3.2
Appc CLI NPM: 4.1.0
Appc CLI Core: 4.1.2
Xcode: 6.4, 7.0-b4
Device: iPhone6 Plus (v8.3), iPhone Simulator v8.4, v9.0
